value.title: Dana Carvey's Joe Biden Impression on Colbert Praised As 'Perfect'
value.excerpt: Dana Carvey appeared as Joe Biden for a full-interview with Stephen Colbert on The Late Show. His impression of the President went down well with fans.

value.title: VP Kamala Harris Announces Small Business Program: "We Must Re-Imagine Our Economy"
value.excerpt: AP: Vice President Kamala Harris announced Tuesday that the Biden administration is distributing $1.25 billion to hundreds of community lenders in an effort to help boost the economic recovery from the coronavirus for small businesses and disadvantaged business owners.

value.title: Biden gives awkward fist-bump to Turkey’s Erdogan at NATO summit
value.excerpt: President Biden on Monday offered an awkward fist-bump to Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan in Belgium at the annual NATO summit Monday — as the Islamist strongman prepared to blast the U.S. leader for his recent recognition of the Armenian genocide.

value.title: Biden says NATO must protect against 'phony populism'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Monday called on foreign leaders to protect against those who prey on division and push "phony populism," asserting that it's up to democratic nations to prove to the world that democracy can prevail and autocracies cannot "deliver for the needs of our people."

value.title: Liberals tell Breyer to retire after McConnell says he won't support Biden Supreme Court pick in 2024
value.excerpt: Some on the left are re-upping their calls for Supreme Court Justice Stephen Breyer to retire from the bench Monday after Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell said he would block a nominee from President Biden in 2024 if Republicans are in the Senate majority.

value.title: McConnell says 'highly unlikely' he would let Biden fill a Supreme Court vacancy in 2024 if GOP wins back Senate
value.excerpt: Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell said on Monday that if his party regains the majority in 2022 it's "highly unlikely" he would let President Joe Biden confirm a Supreme Court vacancy if one opened up in 2024, and was non-committal when asked about an opening at the end of 2023.

value.title: Volodymyr Zelenskyy Hopes Joe Biden Will Give 'Specific' Answer on Supporting Ukraine's NATO Bid
value.excerpt: "I understand that this should be the agreed position of the alliance countries. Nevertheless, we must get clear dates and the likelihood of this for Ukraine," said Volodymyr Zelenskyy.

value.title: Biden calls NATO's common defense pact 'a sacred obligation' amid cyberattacks
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Monday called NATO's Article 5 common defense pact "a sacred obligation" amid the growing global threat of cyberattacks.

value.title: Trump-era sentencing reform law doesn't apply to low-level crack cocaine offenders, Supreme Court says
value.excerpt: The Supreme Court held Monday that a low-level crack-cocaine offender is ineligible to seek a reduced sentence under the Trump-era First Step Act sentencing reform law.

value.title: Comer, Jordan send letter demanding more sunlight on Kerry's role in Biden admin
value.excerpt: House Republicans Jim Jordan and James Comer are demanding answers from U.S. special envoy for climate John Kerry about his role.

value.title: Will Joe Biden polices raise American household income? | Charlotte Observer
value.excerpt: A typical household’s income will grow an additional $36,000 over the next 10 years, says the Biden administration, because of its economic policies. But outside economists disagree with the White House’s assessment.

value.title: Mike Pence Tells Kamala Harris 'It's Time' to Visit Southern Border
value.excerpt: Donald Trump's former VP criticized Harris while tweeting images of him visiting the border during his time in the office.

value.title: Republicans who voted for impeachment face barrage of pro-Trump primary challengers
value.excerpt: Nine out of the 10 Republicans who voted to impeach former President Donald Trump over his alleged role in inspiring the attack on the Capitol by a mob of his supporters are already facing primary challenges – and some of them may have a very hard time holding on to their seats.

value.title: Biden congratulates Israel’s incoming PM Naftali Bennett, vows support for 'Israelis, Palestinians'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Sunday congratulated Israel’s incoming Prime Minister Naftali Bennett after Israel’s parliament voted to approve a new government, effectively ending Benjamin Netanyahu’s historic 12 years in office.

value.title: Media fawning over Joe Biden for ‘return to normalcy’ are missing 'destabilizing effects': Ben Domenech
value.excerpt: The mainstream media has spotlighted President Biden for replacing Trump, The Federalist founder Ben Domenech argued on "Media Buzz."

value.title: Biden says 'very gracious' queen 'reminded me of my mother'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden and first lady Jill Biden visited Queen Elizabeth II at Windsor Castle on Sunday, and afterward the president told reporters traveling with him that the 95-year-old monarch was “ve

value.title: Did COVID-19 Start In A Chinese Lab? Former Trump Official Gives Bold Answer
value.excerpt: In an interview with Fox News, the former secretary of state said he strongly believed Covid-19 originated from a Chinese lab.

value.title: Carl Bernstein: Trump And "Enthralled" Republican Party Are Guilty Of Crimes Against Democracy
value.excerpt: Key Watergate figures Carl Bernstein and John Dean explain the differences between former Presidents Donald Trump and Richard Nixon following reports the Department of Justice under Trump demanded data on 73 phone numbers and 36 email addresses related to lawmakers.

value.title: DOJ sought account information of top Trump White House lawyer: report
value.excerpt: Apple informed former Trump administration White House counsel Don McGahn that the Justice Department subpoenaed information about an email account of his in 2018, and forbade Apple from letting him know, according to a New York Times report.

value.title: Lawmakers react to Trump DOJ subpoenas of Schiff, Swalwell
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi (D-Calif.) and other lawmakers responded June 13 to revelations about acts by former president Donald Trump's Justice Department.

value.title: Pompeo says Biden admin is taking America back to Obama years when 'America was weak'
value.excerpt: Former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Sunday said that when he hears the Biden administration talking about “taking America back" he said they are talking about taking the United States back to the years when “America was weak” during the Obama administration

value.title: Andy Slavitt faults Trump administration for "deadly sins" at start of pandemic
value.excerpt: Andy Slavitt, the former senior White House COVID-19 adviser, says the Trump administration made costly mistakes at the beginning of the pandemic.

value.title: Biden to face questions about rallying allies against China's Uyghur treatment
value.excerpt: President Biden could face questions about his progress convincing allies to publicly call out China over its Uyghur reeducation camps.

value.title: Mike Pence, Wife Buy Suburban Indianapolis Home for $1.93M
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence and his wife have purchased a $1.93 million suburban Indianapolis house that sits on a 5-acre spread and features seven bedrooms, a swimming pool and an indoor basketball court.

value.title: Lara Trump Urges Americans Living at Southern Border to 'Arm Up, Get Guns'
value.excerpt: Lara Trump, former President Donald Trump's daughter-in-law, on Saturday night urged Americans living at the southern border to "arm up" and "get guns" as she railed against President Joe Biden's immigration policies.
